title: C-M’s Hostetter, L-S’ Kuhlmann claim SICL titles
text:
C-M’s Hostetter, L-S’ Kuhlmann claim SICL titles Lynnville-Sully girls claim third straight team championship Published: Friday, Oct. 16, 2015 10:45 a.m. CDT By Troy Hyde Newton Daily News 
SIGOURNEY — Colfax-Mingo’s Dakota Hostetter and Lynnville-Sully’s Canyon Kuhlmann both ran in the state cross country meet last season. 
They are both expected to return to Fort Dodge later this month. Before that, Hostetter and Kuhlmann showed off their talents at the South Iowa Cedar League Cross Country meet and both returned home with individual conference titles. 
Kuhlmann was runner-up during his sophomore and junior seasons but finally got over the hump Thursday. Hostetter was one of three Tigerhawk females to claim all-conference honors as Ilia Hostetter was seventh and Colleen Craig earned honorable mention honors in 11th. 
Lynnville-Sully won a third consecutive girls team title with 41 points. That was 18 points better than Colfax-Mingo as the Tigerhawks were runner-up in their first SICL meet. Sigourney (74), BGM (97), Montezuma (106) and Belle Plaine (124) rounded out the field. 
Ida Byggeth, Marissa Vos and Kasiah Ehresman all landed on the all-conference team for Lynnville-Sully. Byggeth finished second, Vos was third and Ehresman ended up seventh. 
On the boys side, Kuhlmann’s win helped the Hawks to a seventh-place finish. 
Colfax-Mingo’s Cameron Warner was another area all-conference runner as he crossed in 11th, but the Tigerhawks finished eighth in the eight-team field with 112 points. 
Sigourney won the team title with 56 points, while Belle Plaine was the runner-up with 75 and Montezuma was third with 86. English Valleys (99), BGM (126), North Mahaska (129) and Lynnville-Sully (140) rounded out the field. 
Official results — times and individual placings — were not available at press time. 
Both Lynnville-Sully and Colfax-Mingo run in a Class 1A state qualifier at 4 p.m. Thursday at Ankeny Centennial.
